ature appears-and disappears-in contemporary American culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 4aMcSweeney's. 4acontemporary fiction. 4acontemporary literature. 4acreative writing. 4adigital literature. 4ahistory of publishing. 4aliterary sociology. 4anetworks. 4aperiodicals. 4asmall presses. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070397940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080479942340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804799423423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804799423.jpg  a978-3-11-070397-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles